itemDescription.value: Physicist and FRS; first Principal of Chelsea Polytechnic (1845-1931)
Leading ecologist and Professor of Forestry and Natural Resources at the University of Edinburgh from 1975 to 2001
Professor of Genetics at the University of Edinburgh
Research Cell Biologist, University of California, Berkeley (1931-2018)
Professor of Molecular Medicine at the University of Exeter
Emeritus Professor of Developmental Biology, Institute of Cancer Research, Governor of the Wellcome Trust
head of  Imperial Cancer Research Fund Laboratory, Mill Hill, England; (1899-1978)
Scottish physician, botanist and author, 28 November 1867 - 10 February 1926
George Sinclair Professor of Mathematics, School of Mathematics and Statistics, University of Glasgow
Director of the UK Geological Survey
British electrical and mechanical engineer and inventor (1923-1992)
English nuclear physicist and public servant (1921-2008)
Professor of Organic Chemistry, since 1990, Alfred Capper Pass Professor of Chemistry, since 2005 at the University of Bristol
Professor of Chemistry at Heriot-Watt College
